## feedback edge set
* [â†—](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10791689/how-to-find-feedback-edge-set-in-undirected-graph) Let $G=(V,E)$ be an undirected graph. A set $F \subseteq E$ of edges is called a feedback-edge set if every cycle of $G$ has at least one edge in $F$.
